The paper deals with information theory and its application to complex systems, particularly in neuroscience. The paper discusses partial information decomposition (PID) and its implications for measures of information transfer and complexity. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
